Step 1: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees FC). In 3-quart saucepan, melt Becel(R) Buttery Taste margarine over medium-high heat and cook onion, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until starting to brown. Add garlic and cook for 30 seconds. Stir in flour and cook, stirring, 1 minute. Gradually whisk in milk, and bring to a boil. Add broth and return to boil for 1 minute. Add herbs and black pepper. Remove from heat and stir in 4 oz. (125 g) cheese; set aside. Step 2: In 13x9-inch shallow casserole dish, lightly sprayed with non-stick spray, arrange of the potatoes in overlapping pattern. Stir cheese mixture and pour half over potatoes. Repeat with remaining potatoes and cheese mixture. Step 3: Bake uncovered for 45 minutes. Combine remaining cheese and breadcrumbs and sprinkle over potatoes. Bake additional 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender and top is golden brown. Nutritional Facts Calories (Kcals): 140 % Daily Value Total Fat: 3.5g Saturated fat: 1g Trans Fat: 0g Polyunsaturates: 1.0g Omega-6: 0.7g Omega-3: 0.2g Monounsaturates: 0.5g 5% 5% Cholesterol:5mg 2% Sodium:170mg 7% Potassium: 508mg 11% Total Carbohydrate: 21g Dietary Fibre: 2g Sugars: 1g 7% 8% Protein: 7g Vitamin A: 4% Vitamin C: 35% Calcium: 15% Iron: 6% Preparation Time: 20 minutes Cook Time: 55 minutes Total Time: 75 minutes http://www.becel.ca/en/becel/HeartHealthyRecipes/Side-Dishes/Cheesy-Scalloped-Potatoes.aspx